---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Veltro — The Namespace-Resident AI Agent | InferNode" description="Veltro is an AI agent that lives in your namespace, not inside an application. Provably contained, autonomously capable, and composable across devices.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 -top-24 mx-auto h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-accent/10 blur-3xl"></div>
      <div class="relative">
        <p class="mb-6 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">Veltro</p>
        <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          An agent that lives<br />in your namespace.
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
          Not inside an application. Not on someone else&rsquo;s cloud. Veltro runs in a
          namespace you control&mdash;with access to only what you grant and the freedom to
          act autonomously within those boundaries.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
          <a
            href="/#quickstart"
            class="rounded-lg bg-accent px-8 py-3 font-medium text-white transition hover:bg-accent-glow"
          >
            Get Started
          </a>
          <a
            href="/manifesto"
            class="rounded-lg border border-border px-8 py-3 font-medium text-text-muted transition hover:border-accent hover:text-text"
          >
            Read the Manifesto
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What Veltro Is -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">What Veltro Is</p>
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        The namespace-resident agent.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
        <p>
          Most AI agents live inside applications. They inherit the application&rsquo;s
          permissions, depend on its APIs, and are limited to whatever capabilities the
          developers chose to expose. The agent is a feature, not an entity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Veltro is different. It lives in a <strong class="text-text">namespace</strong>&mdash;an
          isolated view of the world constructed from only the resources you explicitly share.
          Files, devices, LLMs, network services&mdash;if it can be represented as a file,
          Veltro can compose it into a capability. No SDK. No API wrapper. No platform
          dependency.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because the namespace defines what exists for the agent, Veltro does not need
          guardrails to prevent it from accessing things it shouldn&rsquo;t. Those things
          simply <strong class="text-text">do not exist</strong> in its world. This is not a
          restriction&mdash;it is liberation. A provably contained agent is one you can trust
          with real autonomy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">How It Works</p>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
          Mount. Grant. Run.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Terminal visualization -->
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface font-mono text-sm overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border px-4 py-3">
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-rpi/60"></div>
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-llm/60"></div>
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-jetson/60"></div>
          <span class="ml-2 text-xs text-text-muted">veltro session</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 space-y-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # 1. Mount the LLM service into the namespace</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> mount -A tcp!127.0.0.1!5640 /n/llm</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # 2. Start the tool server with chosen capabilities</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> tools9p read list find search</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # 3. Run Veltro with a task</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> veltro -p /n/local/docs 'Summarise Q4 results and find gaps'</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-node-jetson">  Q4 revenue grew 18% YoY. Three gaps identified:</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-node-jetson">  1. APAC pipeline down 12% ...</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # Or start an interactive session</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> repl</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Three step cards -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent">1</div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Mount</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
            Mount the LLM service at <code class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">/n/llm</code>
            via 9P. Ollama, Anthropic, or any backend&mdash;the agent sees a filesystem,
            not an API.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent">2</div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Grant</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
            Start <code class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">tools9p</code> with only the
            tools you choose. The agent&rsquo;s namespace is restricted to exactly what you
            grant&mdash;nothing more.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent">3</div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Run</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
            Give Veltro a task and it executes&mdash;reading files, invoking tools, querying
            the LLM, and spawning sub-agents as needed. Single-shot or interactive REPL.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Capabilities -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">Capabilities</p>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
          Built for autonomous work.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#9632;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Namespace-Isolated</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Each Veltro instance sees only the resources you mount into its namespace.
            No ambient authority, no inherited credentials, no attack surface. Isolation
            is not enforced by policy&mdash;it is structural.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#9654;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Sub-Agents</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Veltro can spawn child agents with a subset of its own capabilities. Each
            sub-agent gets a further-restricted namespace. Delegation without escalation&mdash;the
            principle of least privilege, applied recursively.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#8902;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">LLM as Filesystem</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Mount any language model at <code class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">/n/llm</code>
            via llm9p. Write a prompt to <code class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">/n/llm/0/ask</code>,
            read the completion back. Claude, Ollama, any backend&mdash;the agent sees files, not APIs.
            Swap providers without changing a line of code.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#9673;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Multi-Device</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Veltro runs on a Raspberry Pi, a Jetson, a laptop, or a server. Mount resources
            from any device on the network into the agent&rsquo;s namespace using 9P. The
            agent doesn&rsquo;t know or care where the data lives&mdash;it just works.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Security -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="grid items-start gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">Security</p>
          <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
            Provably contained.<br />Mathematically verified.
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted">
            <p>
              Veltro&rsquo;s security is not based on guardrails, content filtering, or
              allow-lists. It is based on the structural impossibility of accessing resources
              that do not exist in the agent&rsquo;s namespace.
            </p>
            <p>
              A prompt injection attack cannot read your SSH keys because in the agent&rsquo;s
              namespace, SSH keys do not exist. There is nothing to exploit. This is not a
              claim&mdash;it is a provable property of the isolation model.
            </p>
            <p>
              The result: you can give Veltro <strong class="text-text">more autonomy</strong>,
              not less. More tools, more data, more freedom to act&mdash;because the boundaries
              are proven, not hoped.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <h3 class="mb-6 text-lg font-semibold">Formal Verification</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-text">TLA+</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Temporal logic specification of namespace isolation invariants. Proves that no sequence of operations can violate containment.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-text">SPIN</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Model checking of the 9P protocol interactions. Exhaustive state-space exploration confirms no reachable state violates isolation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-1 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-text">CBMC</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Bounded model checking of the C implementation. Verifies that the code matches the formal specification.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Headless or Interactive -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">Deployment</p>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
          Headless or interactive. Your choice.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
          Veltro is the agent. How you interact with it&mdash;or whether you interact
          with it at all&mdash;is up to you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- Headless -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#9654;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Headless</h3>
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-medium text-accent">No UI required</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Run Veltro as a background service. Feed tasks through the filesystem,
            read results when ready. Ideal for automation, pipelines, and
            server-side workloads.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Xenith -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-node-jetson/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-node-jetson">&#9638;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Xenith</h3>
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-medium text-node-jetson">Developer power tool</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            A text environment where you and Veltro work side by side. Every agent
            action is observable in real time through the 9P filesystem interface.
            Built for developers who want full visibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stelle -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-node-cloud/10">
            <span class="text-lg text-node-cloud">&#9733;</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Stelle</h3>
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-medium text-node-cloud">Voice-first workspace</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Talk to your computer. Stelle replaces the desktop with a conversational
            AI environment powered by Veltro. Speak naturally, the agent acts. No
            applications to learn.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-32 max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Give your agents real autonomy.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-xl text-lg text-text-muted">
        Veltro is open source, MIT licensed, and runs on any system you control.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
        <a
          href="/#quickstart"
          class="rounded-lg bg-accent px-8 py-3 font-medium text-white transition hover:bg-accent-glow"
        >
          Get Started
        </a>
        <a
          href="/manifesto"
          class="rounded-lg border border-border px-8 py-3 font-medium text-text-muted transition hover:border-accent hover:text-text"
        >
          Read the Manifesto
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
